        <div class="topic-block">
            <div class="topic-block-body">
                @await Component.InvokeAsync("Widgets.ImpactoNavigation", new { active = "Organisation" /* or "Outcome"/"Dashboard"/etc. */ })
                <h3>Step 4 of 6 - Outcomes</h3>
                <div class="stepDesc">
                    <div class="steptitle">
                        What are outputs?
                    </div>
                    Outcomes are the longer-term changes or benefits your project helps to create for people, communities or systems. These could include things like improved confidence, better health, increased skills, stronger relationships or reduced isolation.
                    Outcomes are what happens as a result of your activities - not just what you do, but the difference it makes.
                </div>
                <div class="stepDesc">
                    <div class="steptitle">
                        How to use this section
                    </div>
                    To get started, first tick the project category (or categories) that best describe your project. This will unlock a tailored list of outcomes that are
                    most relevant to your work. From there, you can browse and select the outcomes you’d like to add to your project dashboard.
                </div>
                <div class="stepDesc">
                    If you can’t find something that fits, you can:
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>click ‘view full list of outcomes’</strong> to see everything available</li>
                        <li><strong>contact us</strong> if there’s something important that’s missing - we’re happy to add what you need</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="stepDesc">
                    Once you’ve added your outcomes (and outputs from the previous page), you’ll be able to see them in your <strong>
                        Project Dashboard
                    </strong>. You’ll also be able to download simple,
                    easy-to-use research tools from <strong>My Research Tools</strong> tab to help you track progress and report on your impact.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
